title: Delaware Recording Artists FlowCity Releases New Music Video How I Feel"
text:
Coast 2 Coast Mixtapes announces the release of the new music video by FlowCity currently seeking blog placements and interviews.
Dover, DE (PRWEB) October 07, 2015
Today Coast 2 Coast Mixtapes announces the release of “How I Feel”, the latest music video by Delaware's FlowCity featuring Boney Manyana. The video was directed by A. Young and features production by Yung Rocko. It can be seen in its entirety at the Coast 2 Coast Mixtapes website .
FlowCity is currently seeking press opportunities, interviews, features, and more. They can be reached through their official website .
About FlowCity: Originally formed in 2008, the FlowCity movement is a ground breaking alternative hip hop band from Dover, Delaware that is ready to move to the head of the class in the new age of rappers, lyricists, and producers and engineers. FlowCity is Yung Rocko (Darien Williams), Brownie (Danielle Johnson), and Nino Nosay (Dexter Brown). The three artist bring a wide array of fresh sound, great energy, and great vibes to hip-hop music. After teaming up with Dj Elegal, FlowCity has been blowing up the stage and making new fans everywhere they perform. FlowCity has opened for mainstream artists including: Meek Mill, Travis Porter, Kirko Bangz, Lloyd Banks, Dricky Graham, Bei Major, and Miguel.The FlowCity sound will immediately cross demographic lines, racial barriers, and simply put just "feel good music" into the mix. For more info on FlowCity visit their official Facebook page .
About Coast 2 Coast Mixtapes:
Coast 2 Coast Mixtapes are the most widely distributed mixtapes in the world, with over 100 million downloads/plays generated by over 300 volumes officially hosted by major artists. Coast 2 Coast has a solid reach in the new music industry with a digital magazine, DJ coalition, industry tips blog, yearly convention, and more. Coast 2 Coast Mixtapes represents a unique opportunity for artists of all urban genres, from major to indie. For more information, visit http://www.coast2coastmixtapes.com .
